The paper discusses the use of machine learning models and neural networks for fair decision making, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of incorporating fairness constraints into machine learning algorithms, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for enforcing fairness constraints in neural networks, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
